title: The Astros tie up World Series 2-2 after combined no-hitter | Top of the Order

media:group.media:title: The Astros tie up World Series 2-2 after combined no-hitter | Top of the Order
media:group.media:description:
Cristian Javier throws 6 flawless no-hit innings. The Astros complete the first combined no-hitter in World Series history. Alex Bregman makes history when he fires off a 2-run double to help Houston even up the series in Game 4 of the World Series.
